stylometry: It is more difficult to solve integer programming models because constraints must be satified in order to assign a 0 or 1 to the outcome. Each input varaible will therefore have its own set of constraints in order for excel to assign an integer. This also creates a yes/no scenario in which if any of the constraints are not satified the system automatically assigns it a 0. The end result is not an exact solution but instead a classification. Algorithm searches through millions of solutions to find the correct or most correct solution. We have to consider in Excel when dealing with 0-1 models that the answer obtained may not be the best answer.
